snippet.textDisplay: Gray would never resort to iced shell that quickly, the only two times he's tried to use it was to stop lyone and to save Natsu life. Plus Gray may have been shown losing in this Verizon and I respect the hell out of Esdeth to hell, she is  my second favourite character out of akame ga kill but Gray could eat all ice which means all of that power of Esdeths storm she created would have gone straight to him, not to mention silver didn't have to eat the ice like Natsu eating fire and gajeel eating iron. In both the anime and manga it shows Silver blocking Grays attacks and eating the ice with his mouth a bit away meaning any incoming ice attacks would instantly turn to ice. It didn't work on Intel to begin with because of that chain. If Gray couldn't eat the ice Esdeth would have won in my opinion but because Gray could eat it with just making contact to it it doesn't matter how much more stronger Esdeths attacks are if he can take all of that power for himself  not to mention his magic was created to slay demons, beings that could do feats such as freezing time which means he would have had some way of combatting that, and either way Esdeth can freeze time but it makes sense that she does that with ice itself so again Gray could eat it, and at the end where she throws ice at him, it doesn't matter how much more stronger she was, it should have came down to Gray could eat it all before it effected him. Don't get me wrong Esdeth is amazing and the is way stronger than Gray but it doesn't matter how stronger you are, if there is a broken mechanic such as eating the ice immediately then there should have been no way for her to win with that mechanic. And the whole thing about Gray, he would have never acted like that, he wouldn't have gone for the clones at all, he wouldn't have dissed Juvia ( read 100 years quest ) and he definitely wouldn't have thrown his life away that easily, his catch phrases were off and his personality didn't feel like him at all, although that Esdeth reminded me of the real thing and that was amazing.

snippet.textDisplay: Hold up,  not that i dissagree with the end result (especially bc of Esdeaths time stop) but if a) Gray can control other everything ice as an ice deamon slayer, and Esdeath's timestop literally works with ice, wouldnt it have been kinda useless in the first place? And B) Most of what was presented for Esdeath required a few days to prepare, and I remember the battle between Batman and Spiderman where most of the premise of Batman losing was the fact that he couldnt prepare for the battle. I ask this because, in both instances, the preparation time was very much emphasized upon. Thank you and keep doing good work.
